  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. It&rsquo;s given that Josie purchased a pass to tour a nature preserve and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> identical stickers for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 62.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>62.00</mn></math> total. It's also given that the pass cost <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 19.50\"><mo>$</mo><mn>19.50</mn></math>.&nbsp;Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi></math> represent the cost, in dollars, of one sticker. This relationship can be represented by the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"19.50 plus 10 x equals 62\"><mn>19.50</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>62</mn></math>. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"19.50\"><mn>19.50</mn></math> from both sides of this equation yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10 x equals 42.50\"><mn>10</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>42.50</mn></math>. Dividing both sides of this equation by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 4.25\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4.25</mn></math>. Therefore, the cost of one sticker was <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 4.25\"><mo>$</mo><mn>4.25</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the cost of one sticker if Josie purchased <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> identical stickers for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 19.50\"><mo>$</mo><mn>19.50</mn></math>, not a pass and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> identical stickers for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 62.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>62.00</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice C is incorrect. This is the cost of one sticker if Josie purchased <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> identical stickers for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 62.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>62.00</mn></math>, not a pass and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"10\"><mn>10</mn></math> identical stickers for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"dollar sign 62.00\"><mo>$</mo><mn>62.00</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>Choice D is incorrect and may result from conceptual or calculation errors.</p>",
